==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: moa
<hw>mo"a</hw> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧"⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several very large
extinct species of wingless birds belonging to <gen>Dinornis</gen>, and
other related genera, of the suborder <ord>Dinornithes</ord>, found in
<country>New Zealand</country>. They are allied to the apteryx and the
ostrich. They were probably exterminated by the natives before
<country>New Zealand</country> was discovered by Europeans. Some species
were much larger than the ostrich.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moabite</ent>⟦br⟧
